  "Scope": [{
   "name": "Scope 1",
   "Agent": "Agent 1"
  }],
  "QualifyingCondition": [],
  "SLO": [{
   "name": "SLO 1",
   "BoolExpression": {
    "type": "Comparison",
    "QoSMetric": "AVG TTFT",
    "operator": "LESS",
    "value": 1
   }
  }]
 }],
 "DerivedQoSMetric": [{
  "name": "AVG TTFT",
  "description": "description",
  "metric_type": "TTFT",
  "unit": "sec",
  "uncertainty": 0,
  "window": 10,
  "window_unit": "MESSAGE",
  "aggregation": "AVG",
  "Provider": "Provider 1"
 }],
 "Provider": [{
  "name": "Provider 1",
  "confidence": 0.95,
  "reputation": 50
 }],
 "Agent": [{
  "name": "Agent 1",
  "description": "description text",
  "url": "agent_url",
  "ModelCard": "GPT 4o"
 }],
 "ModelCard": [{
  "name": "GPT 4o",
  "model_card": "..."
 }]
}


Code Annotations:

1. Lines 2–17 (GuaranteeTerm): Defines "Scope 1" and "SLO 1." It mandates that the metric "AVG TTFT" must be LESS than 1 second.
2. Lines 18–28 (DerivedQoSMetric): Defines "AVG TTFT" as a 10-message rolling average. It links to Provider 1 via Rule 5 (Association by name).
3. Lines 29–33 (Provider): Details the source of the measurement, noting a confidence level of 0.95—essential for establishing the reliability of the telemetry.
4. Lines 34–39 (Agent): Identifies "Agent 1" and provides the URL for communication, linking it to its specific intelligence profile.
5. Lines 40–43 (ModelCard): The "GPT 4o" model card. By including this here, the agreement becomes a complete, self-contained audit trail for the AI's behavior and provenance.
